00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:09,120
{\an8}…that your mom's a bad person.

2
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:11,240
{\an8}She's dating many guys at once.

3
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,160
{\an8}Kongkwan, don't!

4
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,480
{\an8}Did you just push me?

5
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,320
{\an8}- Satang, calm down!
- Satang, Satang!

6
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,720
{\an8}- Satang!
- Everyone, stop!

7
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,360
{\an8}…and what I experienced firsthand only.

8
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:26,520
{\an8}And the company
that will sign a contract with us

9
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,480
{\an8}is…

10
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,880
{\an8}Mook and I aren't what you think we are!

11
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,840
{\an8}Then what's this?

12
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,840
Mook.

13
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,360
Thank you for taking care of her.

14
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:09,120
Come on, Mook. I'll drive you home.

15
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,560
I can drive her.

16
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,560
It's pretty late.

17
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:22,080
I don't want to bother you.

18
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,240
You both don't have to drive me.

19
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,360
I can go home myself.

20
00:03:27,440 --> 00:03:28,560
- No.
- No.

21
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,360
You should go home, Boss.

22
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,440
I don't want Ms. Primprao
to misunderstand us.

23
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:45,960
Mook, I'm sorry about what happened.

24
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,840
I never thought she'd go that far.

25
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,520
It's alright, Boss.

26
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,400
I'm just tired today.

27
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,240
I don't want to get into any more fights.

28
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,240
Here you go.

29
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:34,680
Don't worry. I'll drive her home safely

30
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:38,440
because I care about her
no less than you do.

31
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:32,680
Thank you for driving me.

32
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,480
Wait.

33
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:42,920
Besides being your customer,

34
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,160
can I also be your friend?

35
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,640
Can we really be friends?

36
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,280
Of course.

37
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,400
And right now,

38
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:03,280
you really need someone
to listen to your problems

39
00:06:04,280 --> 00:06:06,000
and ease your pain.

40
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,000
And…

41
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,120
I want to be that person.

42
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,320
Uh…

43
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:35,640
Well… I'd better go.

44
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,800
Good night, Mook.

45
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:46,840
Good night.

46
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:22,200
{\an8}MOOK

47
00:07:22,280 --> 00:07:23,520
{\an8}CALLING…

48
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,280
<i>Are you sleeping?</i>

49
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,520
Are you leaving?

50
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:08,880
Yes, Mr. Pop.

51
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:11,880
It's Top.

52
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,320
Can we meet again?

53
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:22,920
I'm afraid not. I don't do repeats.

54
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,080
You're still up?

55
00:08:44,159 --> 00:08:45,680
Why didn't you answer my call?

56
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:50,000
Well, I was a bit busy.

57
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:52,720
Hey,

58
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:55,640
what's wrong? You don't sound okay.

59
00:08:56,840 --> 00:08:59,360
It's a long story. I'll tell you later.

60
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,760
Why'd you call me?

61
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,080
I wanted to remind you.

62
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,560
Tomorrow is Ploy's wedding.

63
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:05,760
You remember, right?

64
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:08,080
Of course I do.

65
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:09,800
Are you okay? Need me to pick you up?

66
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:12,840
No. Let's just meet at the wedding.

67
00:09:12,920 --> 00:09:14,920
I'm hanging up now.
Elevator's almost here.

68
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,840
<i>What?</i>

69
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,560
Don't tell me you're at a hotel again.

70
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,480
You know me too well.

71
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,040
Are you my biggest fan?

72
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,800
Would you stop being that single girl

73
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:27,360
who's seeking fun
and sleeping around already?

74
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,280
Find a real partner already.

75
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,600
A real partner like Kuk?

76
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,520
No, thanks. That's nothing but hell.

77
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,240
<i>I'm enjoying this more.</i>

78
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:37,800
A love with no strings attached.

79
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:40,800
Okay. Suit yourself, bestie.

80
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:44,280
I'll see you tomorrow. Bye.

81
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,400
Bye.

82
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,280
NEW MESSAGE FROM THEE

83
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:09,080
<i>Stop missing me and go to bed already.</i>

84
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:19,520
Who called you, Mook?

85
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:21,480
Why the big smile?

86
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:23,920
It's just Khim, Mom.

87
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,880
She was just gossiping like always.

88
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,320
Did you need something?

89
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:32,480
No. I'm just worried about you,
since you're always coming home late.

90
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:34,760
Mom,

91
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,640
I'm sorry.

92
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:39,160
Work's been so busy lately.

93
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,560
Right! Mom,

94
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:42,200
at my company,

95
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:45,040
we just landed a new client.

96
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:47,600
Really? Congratulations, honey.

97
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:51,840
But don't work so hard
you don't have time for your daughter.

98
00:10:51,920 --> 00:10:53,760
Kongkwan's growing up fast.

99
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,560
She needs love and care.

100
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:58,160
She's growing up without a dad,

101
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,680
so I'm especially worried.

102
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,720
Of course, Mom.

103
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:04,560
I'll do my best to take care of her,

104
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:07,000
so she won't feel like
something's missing.

105
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:10,640
- Thank you, Mom.
- Of course.

106
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:30,680
Is your boss' wife really that evil?

107
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,920
She's like a pageant queen
when she's on TV,

108
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:34,760
helping the society and stuff.

109
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:37,160
How come she's like the devil

110
00:11:37,240 --> 00:11:38,560
in real life?

111
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,280
Are you okay, Mook?

112
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,760
Not really.

113
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:46,080
I really don't know
how to make her understand

114
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:48,760
that my boss and I
aren't what she thinks we are.

115
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,800
How could she?

116
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:53,400
Sometimes, even I don't get it.

117
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:57,280
You and your boss are so close
and lovey-dovey to each other.

118
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:00,000
Anyone who sees would find it fishy.

119
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:03,240
Honestly, though,

120
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:06,240
you never caught feelings at all?

121
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:08,280
Hey, of course not!

122
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:10,360
We really are just friends.

123
00:12:10,440 --> 00:12:13,480
Sure, I haven't worked with him that long,

124
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:17,400
yet I find him to be
very understanding and caring.

125
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:19,800
Still, we're just friends. Do you feel me?

126
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:24,160
If you insist
that you're really just friends,

127
00:12:24,240 --> 00:12:25,960
then find a boyfriend,

128
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:29,160
so his wife won't have to be so paranoid.

129
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:31,440
Ploy, I'm not a 17-year-old girl

130
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:35,000
who's still so young and pretty
that all the boys would want me.

131
00:12:35,800 --> 00:12:37,960
That's it. Enough about me.

132
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:39,640
Today's your good day.

133
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:43,200
Let's only talk about good things.

134
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:49,520
Congratulations, Ploy.

135
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,240
You look so pretty today.

136
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,560
Thank you.

137
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:54,840
Really?

138
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,760
You almost can't tell
who's the bride here.

139
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,800
There you go again.

140
00:12:59,880 --> 00:13:01,800
You acted this way at my wedding too.

141
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:05,400
Ploy and I sure can't wait to see
how your wedding will turn out.

142
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,520
Fine. But where's the groom?

143
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,880
I haven't seen him since we came.

144
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:21,920
Top's here.

145
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:31,160
Mook, there's Top, my husband-to-be.

146
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:34,080
He's handsome.

147
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:37,880
<i>Are you leaving?</i>

148
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:38,880
Yes, Mr. Pop.

149
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,600
It's Top.

150
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:44,880
I'm so excited for you.

151
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:47,040
Ploy, your groom's here.

152
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:53,200
- Khim?
- Where's Khim?

153
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,400
Quick.

154
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:57,160
Go ahead, Ploy.
Join the ceremony. It's time.

155
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:58,880
- Okay.
- Go ahead, Pa, Ma.

156
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,040
Ploy.

157
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:04,600
Hi, Pa. Hi, Ma.

158
00:14:04,680 --> 00:14:05,520
- Hi.
- Hi.

159
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,720
Hello.

160
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,640
Go inside, honey.
We'll start the tea ceremony.

161
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:11,960
- Okay?
- Okay.

162
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,080
‪Let's go.

163
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:18,080
Let's go.

164
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:33,880
What should I do? What should I do?

165
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,760
SOMETHING CAME UP AT WORK. GOTTA GO

166
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:07,920
TELL PLOY FOR ME

167
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:35,440
Here.

168
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:01,080
Where's Khim?

169
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:03,440
I don't know. I'll go find her.

170
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,760
Where is she?

171
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:14,320
<i>Something came up at work. Gotta go.</i>

172
00:16:14,400 --> 00:16:15,840
<i>Tell Ploy for me.</i>

173
00:16:15,920 --> 00:16:18,840
Please come take a group photo.

174
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:21,560
- Please.
- In the center, please.

175
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,120
{\an8}Last night, you all must've been shocked.

176
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:49,920
I apologize on my wife's behalf.

177
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:52,720
We're fine, Boss.

178
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:54,960
Mook, however…

179
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,640
She must've been so shocked.

180
00:17:02,160 --> 00:17:03,400
Can I be frank with you, Boss?

181
00:17:05,720 --> 00:17:07,839
This time, Ms. Prao

182
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:11,520
really went too far.

183
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,680
Don't.

184
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:23,839
I apologized to Mook.

185
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,960
I'll make sure it doesn't happen again.

186
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:33,400
Mr. Pat.

187
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:36,640
I've roughly summarized
this year's expenses.

188
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,760
After we signed the contract with The One,

189
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:42,000
our performance figures
have picked up by a lot.

190
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:47,560
Thank you all a lot for this success.

191
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:50,400
Where's Mook, though?

192
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:54,480
She's at her friend's wedding
this morning.

193
00:17:54,560 --> 00:17:57,800
After that, she'll go to a meeting
with Mr. Thee at The One.

194
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:03,520
Then, I'd better go prepare
for this afternoon's meeting.

195
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:04,960
After the meeting ends,

196
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:07,680
Mook and I will update you
on The One's project plan.

197
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:09,680
- Okay, Boss.
- Okay.

198
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:12,000
Then, if you'll excuse us.

199
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:13,240
- Sure.
- Okay.

200
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:16,800
Excuse me.

201
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:30,400
Try me, then. I'll make sure she pays,

202
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,200
and your stupid travel agency
will pay too!

203
00:19:15,720 --> 00:19:16,840
Ms. Mook's not here yet?

204
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:19,680
No.

205
00:19:20,400 --> 00:19:22,280
The meeting's at two, isn't it?

206
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:24,680
It's not time yet, Mr. Thee.

207
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:27,160
I thought she'd be here earlier,

208
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:29,920
since it's an important meeting.

209
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:34,080
Would you like something special
for lunch today?

210
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:37,480
No, thank you. I'm not very hungry.

211
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:39,280
Okay.

212
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:57,200
I'm hungry. Are you almost here?

213
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:58,760
I'm at The One now.

214
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:01,200
Mook.

215
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:05,240
It's not time yet.

216
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:06,560
Should we have lunch first?

217
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,320
<i>I'm so hungry.</i>

218
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:10,320
No!

219
00:20:13,240 --> 00:20:14,400
Where are you right now?

220
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:19,160
I'm down in the lobby,
but do you mind if I have lunch first?

221
00:20:23,800 --> 00:20:24,760
Who was that, Mook?

222
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:26,400
It's Mr. Thee.

223
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:29,240
But it's not time yet.

224
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:39,600
Please enjoy.

225
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:46,120
Mr. Thee, you haven't had lunch either?

226
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,040
I wanted to have it with you.

227
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,120
It's good that you came too.

228
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,040
Yes.

229
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:03,600
Besides talking about
the upcoming press conference,

230
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:05,560
where we'll officially sign a contract,

231
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,840
I also wanted to discuss
something with you today.

232
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:11,960
What is it, Mr. Thee?

233
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:21,400
Excuse me? Mr. Thee wants Mook
to go work at The One?

234
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:25,280
Why does she have to go, Boss?

235
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:27,640
Is Mr. Thee taking over our company?

236
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:30,280
Guys, calm down.

237
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:32,200
I'm not moving to The One.

238
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:35,240
I'll just be there twice a week
to collaborate with them.

239
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:37,280
But I don't get it.

240
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:39,840
We can just do emails, Zoom,
or online meetings.

241
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:40,920
Yeah.

242
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,080
Judging by the situation,

243
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:45,760
we'd better just do what Mr. Thee wants.

244
00:21:45,840 --> 00:21:47,200
But I don't see the need--

245
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:50,360
It's fine. It's probably just temporary.

246
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:51,920
Once everything's all set,

247
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,440
I'll transfer her back here.

248
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:56,600
She's okay with this arrangement too.

249
00:21:59,840 --> 00:22:01,840
- May, for the signing ceremony,
- Yes?

250
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:04,960
can you invite reporters
who work on business and tourism?

251
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:07,200
That way, we can promote our company.

252
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:09,200
Sure. They'll definitely want in,

253
00:22:09,280 --> 00:22:12,200
since Mr. Thee never shows up on TV
or gives any interviews.

254
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:13,200
It'll be easy.

255
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:15,840
As for Whan and Kemtit,

256
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:18,160
please arrange for package tours
with discounts

257
00:22:18,240 --> 00:22:20,560
only for The One's customers.

258
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,840
I want there to be
something special for them

259
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:26,640
because right now, we're about
to be the main vendor for the hotel.

260
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:30,560
So we'll have work
for the rest of the year, right?

261
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:35,880
Awesome! Now I'll be able to pay
my mortgage every month.

262
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,520
I love my company!

263
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,160
This is just the beginning.

264
00:22:39,240 --> 00:22:40,800
The best is yet to come.

265
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:43,240
Let's do this together!

266
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:47,960
Boss.

267
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:50,000
Oh. Right.

268
00:22:51,960 --> 00:22:53,680
- A Round Trip Travel,
- A Round Trip Travel,

269
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:55,680
- we never cancel our tours!
- we never cancel our tours!

270
00:23:00,280 --> 00:23:02,320
What was that? Can you repeat that?

271
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,000
What?

272
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:07,320
A Round Trip Travel,
we never cancel our parties!

273
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:10,120
- Hey! Not parties!
- No!

274
00:23:10,680 --> 00:23:12,160
"We never cancel our tours," Boss.

275
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:40,480
I've set up Ms. Mook's office
as you instructed.

276
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:43,080
It's close to your office, too.

277
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:47,360
I've also finished drafting the contract.

278
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:49,200
Would you like me to mention in it

279
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:52,080
that Ms. Mook
is required to work here too?

280
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:55,280
That's alright. It's a special agreement.

281
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,080
It's off the record.

282
00:23:57,680 --> 00:23:59,640
Yes, sir. Understood.

283
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,760
It's late, Mook. Aren't you going home?

284
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,280
I'm adjusting this year's marketing data

285
00:24:24,360 --> 00:24:26,600
to cater to The One's contract.

286
00:24:27,120 --> 00:24:29,200
I also want to expand our customer base.

287
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:35,320
Thank you, Mook,
for doing this for all of us.

288
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:37,880
My pleasure, Boss.

289
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,080
Honestly, Mook,

290
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,520
I don't feel too good about this.

291
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,280
About what?

292
00:24:57,800 --> 00:24:59,720
About Mr. Thee.

293
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:09,360
You see, I'm glad
that we won The One as a client.

294
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:15,720
But I suspect Mr. Thee
also wants something else besides work.

295
00:25:20,480 --> 00:25:21,640
You know that, right?

296
00:25:21,720 --> 00:25:25,160
That Mr. Thee doesn't
just see you as his coworker.

297
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:32,440
Don't worry.

298
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:36,440
For me, love's not on my mind.

299
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:39,160
I only want to focus on work for now.

300
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:45,520
What about you and Ms. Prao?

301
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:48,040
How are you two doing?
Have you worked it out?

302
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,840
It's still awkward.

303
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:57,840
I think we really are at a dead end.

304
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:03,160
Either way, I'll always support you.

305
00:26:03,240 --> 00:26:04,400
Good luck.

306
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:08,800
Here you go.

307
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:11,720
Just you tonight, Khim?

308
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:25,000
PLOY

309
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:41,920
What should I do? Why am I so unlucky?

310
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,720
PLOY

311
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,840
You're going to see her, aren't you?

312
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:12,080
I'm not letting you go!

313
00:27:12,160 --> 00:27:13,800
Why are you so damn annoying?!

314
00:27:13,880 --> 00:27:15,760
- Don't go!
- Let go!

315
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:17,400
- Mom!
- No!

316
00:27:17,480 --> 00:27:18,800
Go away!

317
00:27:18,880 --> 00:27:19,920
Get out!

318
00:27:20,760 --> 00:27:23,400
- No!
- Don't move!

319
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:26,080
Mind your own business!

320
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:29,000
- I'm scared!
- You're scared?

321
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:44,800
Mook, there's Top, my husband-to-be.

322
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:47,200
He's handsome.

323
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,400
Thank you.

324
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:38,840
Mr. Pitak, this morning,
I want a continental breakfast.

325
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:41,440
I don't want it to be too heavy.

326
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:43,240
And for lunch, can I have…

327
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:46,120
Pardon?

328
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:48,640
Mook, do you want anything in particular?

329
00:28:50,120 --> 00:28:51,760
What's all this about?

330
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:54,840
I thought we're having a meeting
about the signing ceremony.

331
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,200
What's this room?

332
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:58,480
It's your office, of course.

333
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:00,200
We already discussed this.

334
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,240
You have to move here to work,

335
00:29:02,320 --> 00:29:03,760
so I prepared this room for you.

336
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:07,640
- But I think it's--
- Let's talk later. I'm hungry. Let's go.

337
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:09,600
- Hey, Mr. Thee!
- But…

338
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:11,480
What about your lunch?

339
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:15,360
Hey.

340
00:29:19,120 --> 00:29:20,280
Hey, I'm not a kid.

341
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:21,880
You don't have to hold my hand.

342
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:23,400
It's your first day here.

343
00:29:23,480 --> 00:29:25,120
You can't know
the directions better than I do.

344
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:27,160
- This way.
- Good morning, Mr. Thee.

345
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,760
Good morning, Ms. Usa.

346
00:29:31,840 --> 00:29:33,160
What are you doing here so early?

347
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,520
I wanted to see you.

348
00:29:35,600 --> 00:29:39,360
We have a special deal
we wanted to propose to The One.

349
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:43,360
Thank you,

350
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:46,640
but if it's a tour, I'll have to pass

351
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:51,320
because we're officially signing
a contract with A Round Trip Travel.

352
00:29:52,280 --> 00:29:54,000
We can't work with other companies.

353
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,240
Okay.

354
00:29:57,320 --> 00:30:01,240
If there's ever a chance, we hope
Family Tour can be of service to you.

355
00:30:01,320 --> 00:30:04,400
Sure. If you'll excuse us.

356
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:06,200
- Let's go.
- Mook,

357
00:30:06,960 --> 00:30:08,480
can I talk to you?

358
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:14,000
You can go on ahead. I'll meet you there.

359
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:25,080
Didn't think I'd see you here so early.

360
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:29,080
Did you just get here,
or did you stay here last night?

361
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:31,760
I have a meeting
with Mr. Thee this morning,

362
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:34,960
and this is my new workplace.

363
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:40,440
So, I can be here whenever I want.

364
00:30:42,760 --> 00:30:45,640
And I'm not one
to show up at a hotel uninvited

365
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:48,520
to see some guy, like you are.

366
00:30:50,480 --> 00:30:51,960
You're pretty good.

367
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:54,400
No wonder Mr. Anapat's
so possessive of you.

368
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:56,080
After all,

369
00:30:56,160 --> 00:30:59,400
you really throw yourself
into your work, so much so,

370
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:02,640
you'd sleep your way to the top.

371
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:06,360
Mr. Thee isn't like Kuk.

372
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,680
He's smart enough to know
what's good and useful for him.

373
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:13,480
You can keep
your special deals to yourself.

374
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,400
Here's my advice.

375
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:19,240
You'd better work hard
and find a new client.

376
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:33,520
I never thought
she'd use that kind of dirty trick.

377
00:31:34,120 --> 00:31:37,240
I never thought she'd go that far either.

378
00:31:39,240 --> 00:31:40,920
It just makes my blood boil.

379
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:44,320
If they competed fairly,
maybe we wouldn't have lost.

380
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:47,320
But Mr.Thee already decided.

381
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:49,000
He even sent me a confirmation email.

382
00:31:49,080 --> 00:31:50,120
I'm so pissed!

383
00:31:54,280 --> 00:31:57,320
Kuk, we may have lost to her this time,

384
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:59,600
but I think we still have a shot.

385
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,760
What is it?

386
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:04,080
She may have won the deal,

387
00:32:04,600 --> 00:32:06,880
but that doesn't mean she won't fail.

388
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:13,440
<i>If there's nothing else,</i>
<i>I'm going to summarize.</i>

389
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:15,920
Whan will collaborate
with all the reporters

390
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:18,120
and prepare the documents
to give out to them.

391
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:20,320
As for the location,

392
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:24,200
we'll use one of the rooms at The One
so that we can promote the hotel too.

393
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:32,200
Whan, once you have
a list of the reporters,

394
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:33,760
run it by Mr. Thee,

395
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:36,760
in case he wants to add
or change anything.

396
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:41,680
Okay. Mook, as for the tour program,
we're working on it.

397
00:32:41,760 --> 00:32:42,960
Once it's done,

398
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:46,160
I'll run it by you before
presenting it in the meeting.

399
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:47,640
- Great work.
- Thanks.

400
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:50,920
- Mr. Pitak.
- Yes?

401
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:54,560
May I have the information
of the customers at The One?

402
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:57,160
That way, I can plan
a program that suits them.

403
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:58,920
Of course, Ms. Mook.

404
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:00,640
I really appreciate it.

405
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:03,600
Let's call it a day for now.

406
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:10,400
Whan, let's go talk at my office.

407
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:11,920
I have a few more tasks for you.

408
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:12,960
- Sure.
- Thank you.

409
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,960
If you'll excuse me.

410
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:19,240
Let's go.

411
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:37,360
Mook!

412
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:41,200
He gave you a giant office.

413
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:48,560
Did he hire you to move here already?

414
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:50,280
Don't be silly.

415
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:52,840
I told you, I'm working here temporarily.

416
00:33:55,160 --> 00:33:57,280
Why'd he have to do all this, then?

417
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:06,000
He's hitting on you!

418
00:34:07,080 --> 00:34:08,159
Am I right?

419
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:10,679
Am I? Am I?

420
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:13,120
- I knew it. See?
- What are you talking about?

421
00:34:13,199 --> 00:34:14,920
Well, it's weird, Mook.

422
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,800
Normally, you'd yell at me already.

423
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:19,080
If you don't stop talking, I'll do it.

424
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:22,520
Here. Let me see your work.

425
00:34:30,920 --> 00:34:33,120
What's this? I told you to change this.

426
00:34:33,199 --> 00:34:34,679
Why's it still the same?

427
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:39,040
Okay, okay. I'll change it for you.

428
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:39,960
Roger.

429
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,400
Change it. Hurry.

430
00:34:54,679 --> 00:34:56,560
Go ahead, take a seat.

431
00:34:56,639 --> 00:34:57,840
I know!

432
00:34:59,880 --> 00:35:01,360
Very natural.

433
00:35:11,600 --> 00:35:12,520
You look good.

434
00:35:13,160 --> 00:35:15,280
- Wrong side.
- What?

435
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,360
Are you going to edit it,
or do you want a new job?

436
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:23,560
I am, I am! Wow, look at you.

437
00:35:26,640 --> 00:35:29,400
Isn't the screen too tilted? Oh, okay.

438
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:31,320
Didn't want you to hurt your neck.

439
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,640
It was tilted too far.

440
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:35,280
Oh, boy.

441
00:35:37,360 --> 00:35:40,800
Mook's office is so fancy!

442
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,360
It's huge too.

443
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,840
It's as if she's an executive.

444
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:46,160
Really?

445
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:50,240
Could it be Mr. Thee's
already falling for her?

446
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,400
Man…

447
00:35:52,480 --> 00:35:56,200
Why does this kind of thing
never happen to me?

448
00:35:57,080 --> 00:35:59,280
I'm ready to fall for you too, you know.

449
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,240
You interested?

450
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:02,320
Think I'm your friend?

451
00:36:02,920 --> 00:36:04,880
I never wanted to be a friend.

452
00:36:07,920 --> 00:36:11,160
Maybe he has a crush on Mook?

453
00:36:12,360 --> 00:36:13,480
That's right.

454
00:36:14,040 --> 00:36:17,320
Maybe we beat Family Tour because of this.

455
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:21,240
Sis, how could you think that?

456
00:36:21,320 --> 00:36:24,480
We beat them thanks to Mook's skills!

457
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:31,240
Calm down. I was just joking.

458
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:44,120
Here you go.

459
00:36:57,280 --> 00:36:58,680
What do you want for lunch?

460
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,120
That's alright.

461
00:37:00,200 --> 00:37:02,240
I can order something to eat in my office.

462
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:05,000
Are you okay?

463
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:09,680
Ever since you talked to Ms. Usa,
you haven't seemed okay.

464
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:14,800
Nothing happened. I'm okay.

465
00:37:14,880 --> 00:37:17,240
False. I don't believe you.

466
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,840
You're keeping something from me.

467
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:38,440
I just don't want anyone to badmouth us.

468
00:37:40,920 --> 00:37:42,520
I want to be here to work.

469
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:45,080
To be the best at my job.

470
00:37:46,520 --> 00:37:49,880
I don't want any
non-work-related problems.

471
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:58,280
But for me,

472
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:01,640
what's happening is not a problem.

473
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:04,760
It's the answer.

474
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,640
What do you mean?

475
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:13,520
For me, it's the answer.

476
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,880
It tells me how I feel for you.

477
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:21,480
Now I know why I was so worried about you,

478
00:38:22,680 --> 00:38:23,800
why I cared about you,

479
00:38:25,040 --> 00:38:26,320
why I wanted to be your friend

480
00:38:28,960 --> 00:38:30,440
and help you with everything.

481
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:44,760
Now, it's only up to you

482
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:47,200
to find your answer

483
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:52,600
on how you feel about me.

484
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:58,720
But…

485
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:08,200
You don't have to answer me today.

486
00:39:10,600 --> 00:39:11,760
I want an answer…

487
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:17,320
that comes from your true feelings.

488
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:32,960
- Good morning!
- Good morning.

489
00:39:33,040 --> 00:39:35,360
- Right here, please.
- Yes,

490
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:36,920
- right here, please.
- Thank you.

491
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:37,960
- Thank you.
- May.

492
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,320
- Yes?
- We'll get to interview Mr. Thee today?

493
00:39:40,400 --> 00:39:42,840
You will for sure.
After the ceremony, that is.

494
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:46,560
This is the first time
we get to interview him.

495
00:39:46,640 --> 00:39:48,480
Let's go claim our spots.

496
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:50,520
- Thank you.
- I'll meet you inside.

497
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,280
Good morning.

498
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:55,480
- Good morning, Boss.
- Good morning, Boss.

499
00:39:55,560 --> 00:39:56,400
How are we doing?

500
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:57,640
Everything's in order.

501
00:39:57,720 --> 00:39:59,160
So many reporters today.

502
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:01,960
Where's Mook, though?

503
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:03,760
Mook's setting up inside with Whan.

504
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:08,280
Mr. Anapat, may I take a picture?

505
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:09,840
- Sure.
- Please, go ahead.

506
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:12,560
Just him first, please.

507
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:13,640
I'll get yours next.

508
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:17,960
P-Please, go ahead.

509
00:40:19,920 --> 00:40:21,320
- Okay.
- This way too, please.

510
00:40:21,400 --> 00:40:23,280
- Smile, please.
- This way too.

511
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:25,240
- This way, please.
- Perfect!

512
00:40:25,320 --> 00:40:26,720
- One more, please.
- This way too.

513
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,600
- Okay, perfect.
- Thank you.

514
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:30,880
- Looking great.
- This camera too, please.

515
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:33,320
- This one too, please.
- This one too.

516
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:34,440
Smile, please.

517
00:41:03,720 --> 00:41:04,600
Thank you.

518
00:41:04,680 --> 00:41:05,880
Thank you.

519
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:15,760
Is it true that A Round Trip Travel
won this deal

520
00:41:15,840 --> 00:41:19,920
because of a private relationship
between Mr. Thee and Ms. Veluree?

521
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,800
- What's the story?
- Please give us an answer.

522
00:41:21,880 --> 00:41:23,960
- Is it true?
- Is it true?

523
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:26,560
- What's the story behind this?
- Please tell us.

524
00:41:26,640 --> 00:41:28,080
- Is it true?
- Please answer.

525
00:41:28,160 --> 00:41:30,880
- Is it true, Mr. Thee? What's the story?
- What happened?

526
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:32,600
What are you talking about?

527
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:35,360
We won this deal fair and square.

528
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:37,480
But we have solid proof

529
00:41:37,560 --> 00:41:40,200
that Mr. Thee and Ms. Veluree
were together at a hotel.

530
00:41:40,280 --> 00:41:42,520
- Really?
- A hotel?

531
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:44,720
If you don't stop accusing Ms. Veluree,

532
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:46,480
I'll sue you for defamation.

533
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:49,960
Here's the proof.

534
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:51,920
Let me get a shot of that.

535
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:54,080
- This way, please.
- Can I see?

536
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:55,400
She really does have proof!

537
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:58,320
- It's a clear photo!
- What's this about?

538
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:00,320
- Hey.
- Can we get a shot too?

539
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:03,120
That's when Mook was checking out
the hotel with Mr. Thee!

540
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:05,440
How come the reporter has that photo?

541
00:42:05,520 --> 00:42:06,400
So what's this about?

542
00:42:06,480 --> 00:42:08,120
What do we do now?

543
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:10,400
They're being so close in the photo, too.

544
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:12,080
This camera, please.

545
00:42:12,160 --> 00:42:14,520
- This camera too.
- Here too.

546
00:42:15,360 --> 00:42:16,640
They're close to each other.

547
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:18,760
- This camera, please.
- This way too.

548
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:20,240
- This camera.
- They were hugging.

549
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,720
- This camera too.
- This is big.

550
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:26,480
- What's going on?
- What does this mean?

551
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:28,760
- How'd you two meet?
- Mr. Thee.

552
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:32,160
Ms. Veluree and I are seeing each other.

553
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:34,240
What?

554
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:38,680
So, I don't think it strange

555
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:40,560
if we go out together.

556
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:46,760
As for the criteria deciding the winner
of my project, You Are The One,

557
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:50,240
I've prepared the scoresheets

558
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:52,360
used in the contest.

559
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:56,240
We will send the files
to all of you here today.

560
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:59,120
If you have any doubts about the criteria,

561
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:00,840
please inquire with me directly.

562
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:03,920
When did you two start dating?

563
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,600
Yes, since when?

564
00:43:06,200 --> 00:43:07,320
- So?
- Since when?

565
00:43:07,400 --> 00:43:09,120
I think this is a personal matter

566
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:12,240
that has nothing to do with today's event.

567
00:43:13,760 --> 00:43:16,600
So let me just tell you officially

568
00:43:16,680 --> 00:43:18,960
that we're seeing each other.

569
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:22,440
As for you and your agency,

570
00:43:22,520 --> 00:43:25,120
I'll have to press charges,
since you harassed us

571
00:43:25,200 --> 00:43:28,120
and violated both our rights to privacy.

572
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:35,520
Regarding our project,

573
00:43:35,600 --> 00:43:37,280
does anyone have any more questions?

574
00:43:37,360 --> 00:43:39,200
Aren't you worried people will think

575
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:41,920
you were being biased toward her?

576
00:43:42,000 --> 00:43:45,720
- That's right. Someone will think that.
- Please answer us.

577
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:48,320
Let's just say,
once you've seen my criteria,

578
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:51,760
you surely won't have
any doubts about that.

579
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:52,840
Thank you.

580
00:43:54,000 --> 00:43:56,880
- Wait! Please don't go yet!
- Hold on!

581
00:43:56,960 --> 00:43:58,440
Can we please have more time?

582
00:43:58,520 --> 00:44:00,560
- Mr. Thee!
- Please!

583
00:44:00,640 --> 00:44:01,960
- Please talk to us more!
- Everyone!

584
00:44:02,040 --> 00:44:04,960
- Please stop.
- Mr. Thee!

585
00:44:06,400 --> 00:44:07,600
What was that, Mr. Thee?

586
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:10,040
How could you answer them like that?

587
00:44:15,400 --> 00:44:18,480
He was just doing
some quick damage control.

588
00:44:18,560 --> 00:44:21,400
No. I was telling the truth.

589
00:44:27,960 --> 00:44:29,240
I already told you.

590
00:44:31,000 --> 00:44:32,120
Tell me what?

591
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:34,280
That I like you.

592
00:44:42,440 --> 00:44:45,440
Let's deal with the reporters first.

593
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:47,720
They probably won't leave so easily.

594
00:44:51,280 --> 00:44:53,240
Then, you two should stay in this room.

595
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:56,320
Don't give any more interviews.

596
00:44:57,160 --> 00:44:58,200
Is that fine by you?

597
00:45:00,640 --> 00:45:01,880
I'll come with you.

598
00:45:03,160 --> 00:45:04,080
Sure.

599
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:20,720
Never had anyone confess
in front of many people, huh?

600
00:45:22,360 --> 00:45:23,920
It wasn't funny.

601
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:25,920
Do you have any idea what you've done?

602
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:28,880
I am aware, and I know myself well.

603
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:32,760
I won't deny my own feelings.

604
00:45:42,720 --> 00:45:44,320
I really do like you, Mook.

605
00:46:05,280 --> 00:46:07,920
How'd it go? I bet Mook's done for, right?

606
00:46:08,720 --> 00:46:10,960
<i>I'm the one who's done for.</i>

607
00:46:11,040 --> 00:46:12,240
What?

608
00:46:12,320 --> 00:46:14,000
Why? What happened?

609
00:46:14,080 --> 00:46:16,400
<i>Well, Mr. Thee announced on the spot</i>

610
00:46:16,480 --> 00:46:18,960
<i>that he and Mook are seeing each other.</i>

611
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:21,000
<i>And he even threatened me</i>

612
00:46:21,080 --> 00:46:24,920
<i>that he'd sue me for harassment</i>
<i>and violation of privacy.</i>

613
00:46:30,640 --> 00:46:33,840
Isn't that Mr. Theechuda,
the CEO of The One hotel?

614
00:46:33,920 --> 00:46:37,040
All the reporters
are keeping an eye on him daily.

615
00:46:39,400 --> 00:46:41,880
Mook? Dating Mr. Thee?

616
00:46:53,600 --> 00:46:55,520
YOUNG RISING CEO
INTRODUCES THAI GIRLFRIEND

617
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:58,200
FAMOUS CEO, EXECUTIVE OF TJ GROUP
ADMITS TO FALLING FOR "VELUREE"

618
00:46:58,280 --> 00:46:59,360
CEO OF TJ GROUP FALLS FOR THAI GIRL!!!

619
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:00,560
EXECUTIVE OF TJ GROUP FALLS IN LOVE
WITH THAI GIRL "VELUREE"

620
00:47:01,080 --> 00:47:02,160
"VELUREE" 2023'S CINDERELLA - WHO IS SHE?

621
00:47:02,240 --> 00:47:03,720
"VELUREE" TALENTED WOMAN
FROM THE TRAVEL INDUSTRY

622
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:36,040
YOUNG RISING CEO
INTRODUCES THAI GIRLFRIEND

623
00:47:36,120 --> 00:47:37,000
EXECUTIVE OF TJ GROUP FALLS IN LOVE
WITH THAI GIRL "VELUREE"

624
00:47:37,080 --> 00:47:38,160
"VELUREE" 2023'S CINDERELLA - WHO IS SHE?

625
00:47:41,160 --> 00:47:44,160
I fried these spring rolls myself
this morning. Eat up.

626
00:47:44,760 --> 00:47:46,120
- Are you full?
- Thank you, Ma.

627
00:47:46,200 --> 00:47:48,400
You've got to eat the fish too.

628
00:47:48,480 --> 00:47:52,000
Eat it so you'd get smarter
and get more ideas at work.

629
00:47:52,080 --> 00:47:53,680
I bought this grouper myself.

630
00:47:53,760 --> 00:47:56,440
Kuk! Kuk! Did you see this?

631
00:47:56,520 --> 00:47:58,400
I knew I was right.

632
00:47:58,480 --> 00:47:59,520
Look.

633
00:48:03,160 --> 00:48:05,560
She only beat us because of this.

634
00:48:05,640 --> 00:48:06,520
FAMOUS BUSINESSMAN, EXECUTIVE OF CJ GROUP
CONFESSES TO FALLING IN LOVE

635
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:07,520
WITH THAI GIRL "VELUREE"
TALENTED WOMAN FROM THE TRAVEL INDUSTRY

636
00:48:07,600 --> 00:48:08,920
What's wrong, Usa?

637
00:48:09,800 --> 00:48:11,400
It's Mook, Ma.

638
00:48:11,480 --> 00:48:14,680
Her company only won
because she slept with the CEO.

639
00:48:14,760 --> 00:48:16,880
It's all over the news now.

640
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:18,840
Mr. Thee's dating her.

641
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:20,400
Can I see?

642
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:35,200
"Famous young businessman,

643
00:48:35,280 --> 00:48:37,120
executive of TJ Group admits

644
00:48:37,200 --> 00:48:40,120
to falling in love
with Thai girlfriend, Veluree,

645
00:48:40,200 --> 00:48:42,680
talented woman from the travel industry."

646
00:48:43,600 --> 00:48:44,600
Bullshit.

647
00:48:44,680 --> 00:48:46,560
You're just using work as an excuse.

648
00:48:46,640 --> 00:48:48,320
That's what they wrote?

649
00:48:52,920 --> 00:48:55,760
Kuk, you have to do something.

650
00:48:55,840 --> 00:48:58,280
We can't just watch Mook get everything!

651
00:48:58,360 --> 00:48:59,720
I won't stand for this.

652
00:49:04,600 --> 00:49:06,160
I'd better do something.

653
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:28,200
"Insiders are reporting

654
00:49:28,280 --> 00:49:30,560
that Mr. Thee is planning

655
00:49:30,640 --> 00:49:33,440
a shotgun wedding
with Ms. Veluree. The dowry

656
00:49:33,520 --> 00:49:36,000
is said to be enormous."

657
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:38,080
Hey.

658
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:40,360
What's with those sunken eyes?

659
00:49:45,800 --> 00:49:48,080
I was scrolling my phone all night.

660
00:49:48,160 --> 00:49:49,880
I went on Facebook,

661
00:49:49,960 --> 00:49:52,960
Instagram, Twitter, and every single page

662
00:49:53,040 --> 00:49:56,160
posted news about Mook and Mr. Thee.

663
00:49:56,240 --> 00:49:57,680
The more I read, the more I got…

664
00:49:57,760 --> 00:49:59,680
Stressed, right? Me too.

665
00:49:59,760 --> 00:50:01,200
…jealous.

666
00:50:03,080 --> 00:50:04,480
Did you see that part?

667
00:50:05,080 --> 00:50:06,240
Which part?

668
00:50:13,080 --> 00:50:14,880
"The two of us

669
00:50:16,160 --> 00:50:18,480
are seeing each other."

670
00:50:40,080 --> 00:50:42,800
Boss, we're in big trouble.

671
00:50:42,880 --> 00:50:44,480
What should we do, Mr. Thee?

672
00:50:44,560 --> 00:50:48,760
The news that got out
really hurt our stock.

673
00:50:49,600 --> 00:50:50,920
I'm afraid that…

674
00:50:53,400 --> 00:50:54,760
But in just one day,

675
00:50:54,840 --> 00:50:58,200
searches for our hotel
have increased by 20%.

676
00:51:00,200 --> 00:51:03,960
I find this to be
a perfect opportunity for The One.

677
00:51:09,360 --> 00:51:11,920
Mr. Pitak, please ask our sales team

678
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:15,440
to promote our campaigns
and discounted packages online right away.

679
00:51:17,720 --> 00:51:20,440
You're turning the crisis
into an opportunity, aren't you?

680
00:51:22,120 --> 00:51:24,960
Sure. I'll handle it right away, Mr. Thee.

681
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:26,080
Okay.

682
00:51:33,480 --> 00:51:35,400
Did you see the news on TJ Group's stock?

683
00:51:38,520 --> 00:51:42,520
We wanted to apologize to you
for causing you trouble.

684
00:51:44,400 --> 00:51:46,320
Is there any way we can help?

685
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:48,000
I'm glad you're here.

686
00:51:48,080 --> 00:51:51,240
I'm going to launch a special campaign
to promote our hotel.

687
00:51:51,960 --> 00:51:53,360
I would appreciate it

688
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:56,240
if your team can come brainstorm
with our marketing team.

689
00:51:59,000 --> 00:52:01,440
I think we should capitalize

690
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:04,960
on the current trend as much as we can.

691
00:52:05,560 --> 00:52:06,720
Of course.

692
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:09,000
I'll send my team over to help you.

693
00:52:09,080 --> 00:52:10,400
Okay.

694
00:52:13,800 --> 00:52:15,560
- Mr. Pitak.
- Yes?

695
00:52:15,640 --> 00:52:17,640
Please look into that reporter for me.

696
00:52:18,440 --> 00:52:20,040
I want to know how she got the story.

697
00:52:20,120 --> 00:52:22,800
We will sue everyone involved

698
00:52:23,400 --> 00:52:27,120
for violating our privacy
and for the damage they've caused.

699
00:52:27,800 --> 00:52:28,800
Of course, Mr. Thee.

700
00:52:41,480 --> 00:52:44,160
Prao must've had something to do with it.

701
00:52:45,920 --> 00:52:47,440
I never thought

702
00:52:47,520 --> 00:52:50,240
the woman I used to love
could change this much.

703
00:52:55,560 --> 00:52:57,200
Maybe in her eyes,

704
00:52:57,920 --> 00:53:00,240
you've changed too.

705
00:53:00,920 --> 00:53:02,680
That's why it's come to this.

706
00:53:14,920 --> 00:53:18,080
Boss, please don't worry.

707
00:53:18,760 --> 00:53:21,200
I'll talk to Mr. Thee about this.

708
00:53:21,280 --> 00:53:24,240
Once there's different news,
they'll all forget anyway.

709
00:53:25,600 --> 00:53:28,600
But this had nothing to do with you.

710
00:53:31,680 --> 00:53:33,800
I should just go and make things clear.

711
00:53:35,320 --> 00:53:36,960
What do you mean?

712
00:53:37,040 --> 00:53:38,160
What are you going to do?

713
00:53:40,520 --> 00:53:43,560
Problems are meant to be solved,
not for me to run away.

714
00:53:43,640 --> 00:53:44,920
That's what you told me.

715
00:53:47,400 --> 00:53:52,840
I think it's time I faced it for real.

716
00:53:57,600 --> 00:53:59,840
And what do you think about Mr. Thee?

717
00:54:03,960 --> 00:54:05,000
I…

718
00:54:06,320 --> 00:54:07,320
It's alright, Mook.

719
00:54:08,680 --> 00:54:11,560
You don't have to answer
if you're not ready.

720
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:21,200
When two people love each other,

721
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:24,280
everything suddenly looks beautiful.

722
00:54:27,240 --> 00:54:29,080
But when the love runs out,

723
00:54:31,080 --> 00:54:32,920
it all gets so scary.

724
00:54:38,120 --> 00:54:39,360
Don't you think so?

725
00:54:52,560 --> 00:54:53,720
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

726
00:54:53,800 --> 00:54:55,840
- Say hello. Good morning.
- Good morning.

727
00:55:02,240 --> 00:55:04,920
Kongkwan, Mommy has a meeting today.

728
00:55:05,000 --> 00:55:06,480
Grandma will come pick you up, okay?

729
00:55:06,560 --> 00:55:07,560
Okay.

730
00:55:08,400 --> 00:55:09,960
See you later, Mommy.

731
00:55:10,040 --> 00:55:13,320
See you later. Give me a kiss. Here too.

732
00:55:13,400 --> 00:55:14,840
Okay, pay attention in class.

733
00:55:16,600 --> 00:55:17,680
Bye-bye.

734
00:55:31,600 --> 00:55:33,840
Ms. Prao. Ms. Prao.

735
00:55:39,080 --> 00:55:42,000
Let's gossip about Kongkwan's mom
bagging that rich guy.

736
00:55:44,840 --> 00:55:46,520
It came as no surprise.

737
00:55:46,600 --> 00:55:48,360
She's always sleeping around anyway.

738
00:55:51,400 --> 00:55:54,760
But on the news, Mr. Thee said
he'd take it all the way to court.

739
00:55:55,480 --> 00:55:58,720
He said he'd sue everyone who spread
the fake news and even the reporter

740
00:55:58,800 --> 00:56:00,200
from that day.

741
00:56:02,280 --> 00:56:06,360
Do you happen to know
how the reporter got that picture?

742
00:56:07,760 --> 00:56:09,720
I sent it to her myself,

743
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:12,360
and I'm not scared either.

744
00:56:12,960 --> 00:56:14,320
We're telling the truth.

745
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:15,720
Why should we be scared?

746
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:17,720
Am I right?

747
00:56:18,760 --> 00:56:20,200
- Yes.
- Yes.

748
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:25,920
If you'll excuse me,
I have a meeting at the association.

749
00:56:26,000 --> 00:56:27,120
- Okay.
- Okay.

750
00:56:33,120 --> 00:56:35,040
Will we get in trouble too, Oh?

751
00:56:35,880 --> 00:56:37,920
Will Mr. Thee sue us too?

752
00:56:42,440 --> 00:56:44,800
{\an8}Are you alright? You don't look too good.

753
00:56:53,960 --> 00:56:54,880
{\an8}Mom.

754
00:56:58,520 --> 00:57:00,160
{\an8}You just like Mook better than me.

755
00:57:00,240 --> 00:57:02,400
{\an8}This wouldn't have happened
if it weren't for her!

756
00:57:02,480 --> 00:57:04,040
{\an8}It's happened for a while now, Prao!

757
00:57:04,120 --> 00:57:06,280
{\an8}Even before I met Mook.

758
00:57:08,000 --> 00:57:09,320
{\an8}Here comes the real thing.

759
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:14,200
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

